        <p> Ahorn syrup is poured in the (hopefully) clean snow outside. Then it can be wrapped around a wooden stick and you already have a lollipop. However, my need for sugar is covered for the time being. We then looked around a little on the premises, went briefly into the Souvenir Shop before we slide the way back to the bus. </p>
        <p> Back at the hotel we decided to take a short break before we wanted to continue exploring the underground passages of Montreal. Well from only briefly, there were several hours, which we both lazy and discussed about God, the world, politics and press. </p>
        <p> At some point, however, we still set off and ran through the confused corridors and broken down from a shop to shop. After eating something in a mile of feed, bubble tea tried like here. It turned out to be sugar water with a lot of artificial aromas in which a kind of soaked Haribos swim. Very disgusting. Basti&rsquo;s was probably better in terms of taste. </p>
        <p> Back in the Hotel we gave up the artificial taste with beer and cocktails, debated a little further and at some point made our way to bed. </p>
